headlines.description: — The sense of urgency may be similar, but the stakes are different for Chicago and Atlanta on opposite ends of the Eastern Conference playoff standings.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hawks surge late, Young scores 39 points in win over Bulls

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 21 of his 37 points in the fourth quarter, leading the Boston Celtics past the Memphis Grizzlies 120-107 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum nets 37, leads Celtics past Morant, Grizzlies 120-107

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant's shot looked good the whole way, one that would have given the Brooklyn Nets the lead with under a minute left.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant has 31 points in return, but Heat rally to beat Nets

headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham had 22 points and 12 rebounds, Jerami Grant scored 26 and the Detroit Pistons held off Toronto 108-106 on Thursday night for their sixth straight victory over the Raptors.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cunningham has 22 points as Pistons hold off Raptors 108-106

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic and the Dallas Mavericks were the ones trying to hold on in the second half against Golden State.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic scores 41 points, Mavs beat Warriors again, 122-113

events.name: Sacramento Kings at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Harrison Barnes had 27 points and the Sacramento Kings held off San Antonio 115-112 on Thursday night, keeping Spurs coach Gregg Popovich a victory shy of tying Don Nelson’s NBA record.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings beat Spurs, 115-112, keep Popovich shy of NBA mark

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Reggie Jackson scored 12 of his season-high 36 points in the fourth quarter while adding nine assists and eight rebounds, and the Los Angeles Clippers completed a four-game season sweep of the Los Angeles Lakers with a 132-111 victory Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers surge to 132-111 victory, season sweep of Lakers
